      "timestamp": "2026-06-07T07:52:06.06+00:00",
      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "I remember now that there was a solution to the problem that I never got around to implementing \uD83D\uDE05\nMagic keeps the files open to \"lock\" them. Disabling this behavior using `locking disable` should solve the issue once and for all.\n\nI opened a PR here: https://github.com/librelane/librelane/pull/959\nMaybe you could give this a try with the default of 1024 descriptors.\n\nSimply edit `flake.nix` to point to the LibreLane branch you want to use: https://github.com/wafer-space/gf180mcu-project-template/blob/7cbd17465ca1446b4daf93f543f899fb1b3489c3/flake.nix#L12\nAnd update `flake.lock` by running `nix flake update`.",
      "author": {
        "id": "323371864074485771",
        "name": "mole99",
        "discriminator": "0000",
        "nickname": "Leo Moser (mole99)",
        "color": null,
